name: The Hierophant
description: One of the least loved and little understood Tarot cards. And for good reason: it is very complex to interpret. A Hierophant in Ancient Greece was a priest who was in charge of interpreting the sacred mysteries. In that sense, this card speaks to us of the dialogue we maintain with our private gods; a dialogue that reminds us that in active listening (to others and to ourselves) we can access the sacred.
